1 capsicum
1 beef strips
1 Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 couscous
1 vegetable stock powder
1 roasted almonds
1 salad leaves
1 Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin
olive oil

• Boil a kettle of water
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Slice capsicum
• Cook capsicum for 3-4 mins
• Add beef strips and seasoning and cook, tossing, until browned, 2 mins
• Season

• Meanwhile, place couscous in a bowl and crumble over vegetable stock
• Add boiling water (3/4 cup for 2P / 1 1/2 cups for 4P) and stir to combine
• Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork and set aside.
• Pierce a few holes in pumpkin packet and microwave until hot and steaming, 2-3 mins
• Roughly chop almonds

• Toss pumpkin and spinach & rocket with the couscous. Drizzle with oil and season
• Plate up veggie couscous and top with beef, capsicum, dill & parsley mayo and almonds
• Crumble over cheese